Package org.moddingx.libx.datagen.provider.patchouli.page

Interface Content

All Known Implementing Classes:
CaptionContent, RecipePage, TextContent
@Experimental public interface Content
Defines some content for a patchouli book entry. A content is something that can create zero, one or multiple actual book pages, when built. Each book entry will only ever have one single Content. When new content is added to the entry, it is chained to the previous content using with(Content). Subclasses may override this to allow for content to merge on the same page. For example, when a recipe content is merged with some caption content, both of them will result in a single content that adds a recipe page with text.
